UNPATCHED (0x1C0057144 @ 0x1C00578E9):
    flag = Feature_2227659065__private_IsEnabledDeviceUsage();  // bit 0x10 of featureState, else WIL fallback
    if (flag == 0)                                              // feature off (default)
        r8 = (size + 0x1FF) & 0xFFFFFE00;                        // 512-byte round-up
    else
        r8 = GetAlignedBufferSize(this, size);                  // device-sector-aligned
    status = ClfsProbeAndAllocateMdl(AccessMode, buffer, r8, ...);

PATCHED (0x1C0057144 @ 0x1C005790D):
    r8 = GetAlignedBufferSize(this, size);                      // always device-sector-aligned
    status = ClfsProbeAndAllocateMdl(AccessMode, buffer, r8, ...);

GetAlignedBufferSize (0x1C0028CBC, byte-identical in both builds) queries the device geometry via a guarded indirect call (*(*this_dev + 0xF0))() and rounds up:
    if (status < 0 || sector <= 0x200)
        return (size + 0x1FF) & ~0x1FF;   // fallback: 512-byte alignment
    else
        return (size + sector - 1) & ~(sector - 1);  // device-sector alignment (>= 512-byte result)
